func (uc *ActivateEndpointUseCase) Execute(ctx context.Context, endpointID uuid.UUID) error {
```

## Interface Documentation

```go
// EndpointRepository defines the interface for endpoint persistence.
// Implementations must enforce multi-tenant isolation.
type EndpointRepository interface {
    Create(ctx context.Context, endpoint *model.Endpoint) error
    GetByID(ctx context.Context, id uuid.UUID) (*model.Endpoint, error)
}
```

## Comment Style

```go
// ❌ BAD - narrates what code does
// Increment counter
counter++

// ❌ BAD - restates the obvious
// GetByID gets by ID
func (r *Repo) GetByID(...)

// ✅ GOOD - explains non-obvious intent
// GetByID retrieves an endpoint, returning ErrNotFound if it doesn't exist.
func (r *Repo) GetByID(...)

// ✅ GOOD - explains trade-offs
// We use row_to_json() instead of manual scanning to handle
// tables with unknown column schemas dynamically.
```

## Godoc Conventions

- First sentence is the summary (shown in package index)
- Start with the entity name: `// Handler provides API Management HTTP handlers.`
- Use present tense: "creates", "returns", "checks" (not "will create")
- Reference other symbols with brackets: `[EndpointRepository]`

## Checklist

- [ ] Every exported type has a doc comment
- [ ] Every exported function has a doc comment
- [ ] Package has a doc comment (`// Package xxx ...`)
- [ ] Comments explain WHY, not WHAT
- [ ] First sentence starts with the type/function name
